Inquired further to find out source of failure in ptu, customer had concern of fluid leaking from ptu. Checked fluid leak, found silver fluid leaking from ptu. Strongly suspected internals to be destroyed. Removed side cover, found major internal damage. Called Northway Ford, confirmed transfer case fluid replacement interval is every 200,000 km's. Good morning George, thanks for your previous email with the estimate for the replacement of the transfer case and the hvac control panel on Michael's Flex. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, shop supplies and fluids, as well as a $100 deductible + tax. Additionally, our Mitchell Labour Guide allows for 1.0 hour for the replacement of the hvac control panel, so this is the maximum we will be able to contribute for that repair for labour. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$1061.60
Labour-$728.00 (5.6 hours x $130/h)
Deductible-$100.00 + tax
Tax-$219.65
Authorization-JSW27LMR89

Total = $1909.25

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards,

Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster

notes.note:
At Progressive Auto. Bottom end knock. Shop was convinced that the customer did not have enough oil changes done but the customer provided 4 valid receipts for oil changes and although one gap is, in my opinion, to large, the manual only specifies that the oil be changed when the "Service oil" light comes on. No mileage or time restrictions besides. Well, we can only guess when the light came on. 
Shop to source used engine. They are aware of maximum. A.H.
